# Self-curation is mandatory

`agent-docs/` is the living brain of hftr v2. Every session that changes behavior, schema,
decisions, or standards **must update owning docs in the same change**.

## Session start

1. Read `agent-docs/README.md`
2. Read owning doc(s) for the area you touch (see `agent-sources.mdc`)
3. Check active milestone in `plans/master-build-plan.md`

## Same-change updates

| Change type | Update |
|-------------|--------|
| Feature behavior | `product/product-spec.md` or architecture doc |
| Schema/API | `architecture/data-model.md` + contracts |
| UI surface | `ui-ux/ui-spec.md` |
| Tech swap | `research/tech-decisions.md` (new TD-nn) |
| User decision | `dev-intent/decisions-log.md` (D-nnn) |
| Unresolved question | decisions-log "Open" (OQ-n) |
| Milestone progress | `plans/master-build-plan.md` + sprint spec |
| v1 port | `research/v1-carryover.md` |

## Open questions

- Stable IDs: `OQ-1`, `OQ-2`, …
- **Resolve in place** — never delete unanswered questions

## Drift handling

If docs contradict code: code wins for runtime; log drift and fix docs (or file OQ-n if intent unclear).
Invoke skill `.cursor/skills/agent-docs-curate/` or `/curate-docs` for full passes.

## End of run

Doc updates ship in the **same git commit** as the code they describe. After verification passes,
commit via `commit-message` skill — do not leave curated docs uncommitted alongside verified code.
